ints1:\n            for x2, y2 in points2:\n                translation_vector = (x2 - x1, y2 - y1)\n                translation_count[translation_vector] += 1\n        \n        # The maximum value in the dictionary is the largest overlap\n        return max(translation_count.values(), default=0)\n```\n\nThis solution works by first identifying all the positions of `1`s in both images. Then, it computes the translation vectors that would map each `1` in `img1` to each `1` in `img2`. By counting the frequency of each translation vector, we can determine the most common translation that results in the maximum overlap. The result is the highest frequency found, which represents the largest possible overlap.", "estimated_date": 1526169600000}